panels.description:
Test Strength vs. Mutation Coverage tells you whether your strong test suite is also effective at catching the mutations in the code where strong indicate your tests are good at detecting faults. I.e.:
- high Test Strength but low Mutation Coverage: not thoroughly covering all possible edge cases
- high Mutation Coverage but low Test Strength: covering a lot of the code, but the logic is not deeply enough tested.
panels.title: Mutation Coverage and Test Strength
